Nyrstar Pays CEO 1.2 Million Euros in 2010 as Shares Gain 34%

-- B y   F i r a t   K a y a k i r a n
-- 
2011-04-13T09:44:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/nyrstar-pays-ceo-1-2-million-euros-in-2010-as-shares-gain-34-.html
Nyrstar (NYR)  NV, the largest producer of
refined zinc, paid Chief Executive Officer Roland Junck a total
of 1.2 million euros ($1.7 million) in salary, bonuses and
benefits last year as its shares rose 34 percent.  Payments included a 557,912-euro base salary and a 361,443-
euro annual incentive based on his individual performance,
Nyrstar said in the annual report on its  website .  Payments to other members of the management committee
totaled 3.45 million euros, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Firat Kayakiran in London at 
 fkayakiran@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
